146
00:10:51,447 --> 00:10:56,410
When we first took him in, Matthew's
problems seemed less severe.

147
00:10:56,493 --> 00:10:58,830
Now he's in so much pain.

148
00:10:58,913 --> 00:11:04,501
Doctors, clergy, no one has
any idea what's wrong with him.

149
00:11:04,586 --> 00:11:07,630
We heard about your work
with special children

150
00:11:07,714 --> 00:11:09,757
and thought maybe you could help.

151
00:11:09,841 --> 00:11:11,300
Not for free.

152
00:11:12,384 --> 00:11:15,262
His father left a sizeable inheritance.

153
00:11:15,346 --> 00:11:17,556
What about the mother? Is she dead?

154
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:19,516
No, she's...

155
00:11:19,601 --> 00:11:22,645
Well, that's another story. Here we are.

156
00:11:25,815 --> 00:11:29,318
Make the check out to cash.
I'll take it from here.

157
00:11:39,286 --> 00:11:41,580
They think you're getting worse.

158
00:11:42,581 --> 00:11:45,918
But... you're not, are you, kid?

159
00:11:51,090 --> 00:11:53,092
You're getting stronger.

160
00:11:53,175 --> 00:11:56,303
Let's get started.

161
00:12:00,182 --> 00:12:01,768
So what kind of training is this?

162
00:12:01,851 --> 00:12:03,728
You like ice cream?

163
00:12:03,811 --> 00:12:05,437
Yeah.

164
00:12:05,521 --> 00:12:09,358
Then shut up and eat it.
I'll ask the questions.

165
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:12,862
First thing you gotta understand is

166
00:12:12,945 --> 00:12:16,991
nobody feels sorry for
you and nobody ever will.

167
00:12:17,909 --> 00:12:21,162
'Cause when it comes to being born lucky...

168
00:12:21,245 --> 00:12:23,247
you won the friggin' lottery.

169
00:12:23,330 --> 00:12:24,415
I did?

170
00:12:25,374 --> 00:12:27,584
