Smart don't come out of books, kid.

208
00:13:58,217 --> 00:14:03,097
Smart is making the right
decision at the right time.

209
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:06,308
Like now.

210
00:14:06,392 --> 00:14:08,435
What's it gonna be, Matty?

211
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:13,024
You gonna spend your life crying and
rocking yourself to sleep at night?

212
00:14:13,107 --> 00:14:15,985
Or are you gonna dig deep

213
00:14:16,068 --> 00:14:20,782
and find out what it takes to
reshuffle those cards life dealt you?

214
00:14:22,199 --> 00:14:23,534
Your call.

215
00:14:27,747 --> 00:14:30,332
Good choice, kid.

216
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:35,421
No one's bought me ice
cream since my dad died.

217
00:14:35,504 --> 00:14:37,048
What's it taste like?

218
00:14:37,131 --> 00:14:39,091
Vanilla.

219
00:14:39,175 --> 00:14:41,969
Everybody can taste vanilla.

220
00:14:42,053 --> 00:14:45,848
Pay a little more
attention, use those gifts.

221
00:14:45,932 --> 00:14:47,767
You know what you got?

222
00:14:48,851 --> 00:14:51,353
Sugar grains, vanilla bean,

223
00:14:51,437 --> 00:14:56,442
milk from three different
dairies from two states...

224
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:01,155
ugh...

225
00:15:01,238 --> 00:15:04,951
batch of chemicals straight
off the periodic tables and...

226
00:15:07,244 --> 00:15:09,956
dirt off the guy's hand
that served it to you.

227
00:15:11,123 --> 00:15:14,085
He spent his morning gardening.

228
00:15:14,168 --> 00:15:18,172
Whole world around you,
Matty, and it is friggin' huge.

229
00:15:18,255 --> 00:15:19,966
And all you need...

230
00:15:21,258 --> 00:15:23,094
are the guts to let it in.

231
00:15:23,177 --> 00:15:24,720
Try.

232
00:15:24,804 --> 00:15:28,140
That dog, what's his story?

233
00:15:29,934 --> 00:15:31,393
He's hungry...

234
00:15:31,477 --> 00:15:32,937
his stomach's growling...

235
00:15:33,855 --> 00:15:37,817
and he's dying to eat the hot dogs
that guy's carrying just upwind of him.

236
00:15:39,693 --> 00:15:41,278
Not bad.

237
00:15:41,362 --> 00:15:43,655
What about the girl?

238
00:15:45,825 --> 00:15:48,119
Her skin's... Her skin's too hot.

239
00:15:50,496 --> 00:15:52,748
Her heart's beating fast.

240
00:15:52,832 --> 00:15:54,125
Is she sick?

241
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:55,918
Worse.

242
00:15:56,002 --> 00:15:57,378
She's in love.

243
00:15:57,461 --> 00:15:58,963
And the old man?

244
00:16:03,926 --> 00:16:05,177
He's...

245
00:16:07,638 --> 00:16:08,848
He's dying.

246
00:16:08,931 --> 00:16:11,433
And there's nothing you can do about it.

247
00:16:13,269 --> 00:16:17,857
Big world... not all of
it flowers and sunshine.

248
00:16:18,732 --> 00:16:24,113
And the only way guys
like you and me can survive

249
00:16:24,196 --> 00:16:27,992
is to grab it by the
throat and never let go.

250
00:16:29,243 --> 00:16:31,578
If I ask you a
question, will you hit me?

251
00:16:32,204 --> 00:16:33,747
Depends on the question.

252
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:36,918
How did you find me? How did you know?

253
00:16:37,001 --> 00:16:40,546
Old bitty at the orphanage
thinks it's her idea.

254
00:16:40,629 --> 00:16:42,464
But it wasn't, was it?

255
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,427
Maybe it's one of my gifts.

256
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,845
Or you just got lucky.

257
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:50,514
That's not an answer.

258
00:16:53,184 --> 00:16:55,227
You catch on quick.

259
00:16:57,646 --> 00:16:58,898
You're going to help me?

260
00:16:59,481 --> 00:17:01,442
No, I'm gonna train you.

261
00:17:02,693 --> 00:17:06,530
How to control your gift,
make it work for you...

262
00:17:06,613 --> 00:17:09,951
use it, and how to fight.

263
