00:17:12,036 --> 00:17:15,206
Your dad ain't here. You'll
need skills for the war.

265
00:17:15,289 --> 00:17:16,623
What war?

266
00:17:17,249 --> 00:17:21,337
We'll get to that
part... when you're ready.

267
00:17:21,420 --> 00:17:23,630
I don't even know your
name. What do I call you?

268
00:17:23,714 --> 00:17:25,216
Stick.

269
00:17:25,299 --> 00:17:28,885
Are you gonna lie there all
night or get up off your ass?

270
00:17:29,803 --> 00:17:30,972
Jesus, kid.

271
00:17:31,055 --> 00:17:34,308
I'm gone five minutes, you turn
this place into a shit show.

272
00:17:34,391 --> 00:17:35,684
You've been gone 20 years.

273
00:17:37,019 --> 00:17:38,229
What are you doing back in my city?

274
00:17:38,312 --> 00:17:40,314
Your city?

275
00:17:40,397 --> 00:17:42,649
Hell's Kitchen hates your guts.

276
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:46,570
They have you pegged as a cop
killer and some kind of mad bomber.

277
00:17:46,653 --> 00:17:47,904
Yeah, I'm taking care of it.

278
00:17:47,989 --> 00:17:49,740
An old guy just lit you up.

279
00:17:49,823 --> 00:17:51,575
You ain't taking care of shit.

280
00:17:51,658 --> 00:17:53,327
Why are you here?

281
00:17:53,410 --> 00:17:55,329
To save you...

282
00:17:55,412 --> 00:17:58,707
and everyone in the Kitchen
from a horrible death.

283
00:18:00,501 --> 00:18:01,877
More or less.

284
00:18:05,131 --> 00:18:07,841
Paper trail on Union Allied's a bust.

285
00:18:07,924 --> 00:18:09,385
Whoever's pulling the strings

286
00:18:09,468 --> 00:18:12,304
busted up the one big corporation
into a bunch of little ones.

287
00:18:12,388 --> 00:18:13,805
It's an old game.

288
00:18:13,889 --> 00:18:16,850
Spread the records far and
wide, discourage investigation.

289
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:18,935
God. I mean, it's like...

290
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:22,273
It's like trying to straighten
out a bowl of spaghetti.

291
00:18:22,356 --> 00:18:24,316
Well, you could always let it go.

292
00:18:25,234 --> 00:18:27,694
Not gonna happen.

293
00:18:27,778 --> 00:18:29,113
I already told you that.

294
00:18:29,196 --> 00:18:32,158
Stop complaining. This is the job.

295
00:18:32,241 --> 00:18:34,910
Researching, gathering facts.

296
00:18:34,994 --> 00:18:38,830
It's long and boring and complicated,
and half the time you still come up empty.

297
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:43,377
Well, you're just a little ray of sunshine.

298
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:45,296
Just giving you the lay of the land.

299
00:18:46,547 --> 00:18:50,717
For every exposé I've had published,
there were a dozen that didn't pan out.

300
00:18:50,801 --> 00:18:52,511
All right, all right, so I'm
the new girl on the block,

301
00:18:52,594 --> 00:18:54,513
I don't know what I'm doing, I get it.

302
00:18:59,143 --> 00:19:02,146
What about you? What'd you find?

303
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,650
Ah, bits and pieces. Yakuza...

304
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:09,278
Wait, the Japanese mafia?

305
00:19:10,279 --> 00:19:12,906
Triads, too. Drugs, I think.

306
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:18,412
Then there's the bombings
that took out the Russians.

307
00:19:18,495 --> 00:19:22,499
And you think it's all
connected to Union Allied?

308
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:23,959
Doesn't matter what I think.

309
00:19:24,043 --> 00:19:25,877
Only matters what I can prove.

310
00:19:25,961 --> 00:19:29,756
Wait, what about the cops that got shot?

311
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,551
I mean, you really think
that was the guy in the mask?

312
00:19:35,512 --> 00:19:39,015
I was standing right next to
one of them when it happened.

313
00:19:40,392 --> 00:19:42,394
Detective named Blake.

314
00:19:44,230 --> 00:19:46,815
Didn't like each other very much.

315
00:19:46,898 --> 00:19:48,775
Yeah, I met him...

316
00:19:48,859 --> 00:19:51,237
when they brought me into the precinct.

317
00:19:52,238 --> 00:19:53,989
I see why you didn't get along.

318
00:19:54,073 --> 00:19:56,200
Did what I could.

319
00:19:56,283 --> 00:19:58,702
If he comes out of a coma, maybe...

320
00:19:58,785 --> 00:20:02,664
maybe he'll thank me, tell me
what really happened out there.

321
00:20:02,748 --> 00:20:04,666
Till then...

322
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:07,128
the man in the mask pops up...

323
00:20:07,211 --> 00:20:09,963
do me a favor, run the other way.

324
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:13,509
He saved my life, Ben.

325
00:20:14,635 --> 00:20:17,429
How do you know he wasn't
there just to, um...

326
00:20:18,347 --> 00:20:19,931
hurt somebody else?

327
00:20:22,101 --> 00:20:26,062
I... I never... never
thought about it like that.

328
00:20:26,147 --> 00:20:30,901
My experience... there
are no heroes, no villains.

329
00:20:30,984 --> 00:20:32,528
Just people with different agendas.

330
00:20:32,611 --> 00:20:34,321
Yeah, and one of those was to kill me.

331
00:20:34,405 --> 00:20:35,656
Mmm-hmm.

332
00:20:35,739 --> 00:20:36,782
It was.

333
00:20:36,865 --> 00:20:39,618
And you're not careful, maybe
they'll want a second crack at it.

334
00:20:41,787 --> 00:20:45,291
The only way I'll ever feel safe again

335
00:20:45,374 --> 00:20:48,294
is if the people that you are
talking about are put away.

336
00:20:48,377 --> 00:20:51,297
Then we better try harder to
straighten out that spaghetti.

337
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:55,426
So...

338
00:20:56,510 --> 00:20:58,137
if we can connect...

339
00:20:59,430 --> 00:21:03,058
the tenements, and the
shootings, and Union Allied...

340
00:21:03,975 --> 00:21:06,187
that something you'd take to your editor?

341
00:21:07,688 --> 00:21:09,523
Yeah.

342
00:21:09,606 --> 00:21:11,650
Probably bring home a Pulitzer.

343
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:13,444
But, uh, I think it's a long shot.

344
00:21:13,527 --> 00:21:17,448
Well, I was a mean three-point shooter
on my high school basketball team.

345
00:21:17,531 --> 00:21:19,658
I like the long shots.

346
00:21:19,741 --> 00:21:21,535
This isn't a game, Karen.

347
00:21:21,618 --> 00:21:23,912
I... I know that.

348
00:21:23,995 --> 00:21:27,999
Anything happens to
you... it's gonna be on me,

349
00:21:28,083 --> 00:21:29,710
and, uh...

350
00:21:32,879 --> 00:21:35,006
I don't want to be responsible for that.

351
00:21:37,343 --> 00:21:38,802
I can't.

352
00:21:41,513 --> 00:21:42,973
I'll be okay.

353
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,852
They're not gonna win.

354
00:22:21,303 --> 00:22:23,597
What a shithole.

355
00:22:24,723 --> 00:22:26,517
You have any idea what I pay in rent?

356
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,226
Expensive shithole.

357
00:22:29,395 --> 00:22:30,812
You had a woman in here.

358
00:22:30,896 --> 00:22:32,063
That's none of your business.

359
00:22:32,147 --> 00:22:34,316
When's she coming back?

360
00:22:35,191 --> 00:22:36,860
- Never.
- Good.

361
00:22:36,943 --> 00:22:39,783
You got a warped perspective on the
whole good/bad thing, you know that?

362
00:22:40,989 --> 00:22:42,949
Women are a distraction.

363
00:22:43,659 --> 00:22:48,330
Just like... furniture, apartments...

364
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,374
Whoa.

365
00:22:52,709 --> 00:22:54,085
Silk sheets.

366
00:22:54,169 --> 00:22:56,422
Cotton feels like sandpaper on my skin.

367
00:22:57,839 --> 00:23:00,301
You'd be better off
sleeping on real sandpaper

368
00:23:00,384 --> 00:23:03,053
than surrounding yourself
with all this bullshit.

369
00:23:03,136 --> 00:23:06,181
This is my life and I made
something of it, without you.

370
00:23:06,264 --> 00:23:08,392
That's the part that really
pisses you off, isn't it?

371
00:23:08,475 --> 00:23:12,228
No, Matty. No, I'm proud
of you, I really am.

372
00:23:12,313 --> 00:23:16,317
The things you've done, what
you've made of yourself, but...

373
00:23:17,443 --> 00:23:18,652
this is...

374
00:23:18,735 --> 00:23:23,740
Surrounding yourself with soft
stuff isn't life, it's death.

375
00:23:24,741 --> 00:23:27,828
Someday those silk sheets
are gonna crawl up behind you,

376
00:23:27,911 --> 00:23:31,289
wrap themselves around your
throat and choke you to death.

377
00:23:31,373 --> 00:23:32,458
You're a warrior.

378
00:23:32,541 --> 00:23:34,000
Yeah...

379
00:23:34,084 --> 00:23:35,336
that's not all I am.

380
00:23:35,419 --> 00:23:40,382
A warrior, heir to the Spartans,
baddest of the bad-asses.

381
00:23:40,466 --> 00:23:42,468
They knew what they had
to do and they did it.

382
00:23:42,551 --> 00:23:43,594
And what was that?

383
00:23:43,677 --> 00:23:46,137
Cut it loose, all of it.

384
00:23:47,055 --> 00:23:49,475
Cut yourself free...

385
00:23:49,558 --> 00:23:52,811
from the women, the
comforts, the fancy job.

386
00:23:52,894 --> 00:23:54,938
The job's not that fancy.

387
00:23:55,021 --> 00:23:57,691
Do you have friends? People you care about?

388
00:23:57,774 --> 00:23:59,275
Yeah, two.

389
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,487
Cut 'em loose, for their sake.

390
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:04,365
Break their hearts if you
have to, just do it quick.

391
00:24:04,448 --> 00:24:05,616
I'm not gonna do that.

392
00:24:05,699 --> 00:24:08,535
Then they will suffer and you will die.

393
00:24:09,911 --> 00:24:13,499
Relationships are a luxury men
like you and me can't afford.

394
00:24:13,582 --> 00:24:15,000
Is that why you left?

395
00:24:17,085 --> 00:24:18,670
Huh? To protect me?

396
00:24:18,754 --> 00:24:20,422
I had my reasons.

397
00:24:20,506 --> 00:24:21,923
I was a kid.

398
00:24:23,133 --> 00:24:24,593
You still are.

399
00:24:25,719 --> 00:24:27,804
"Boo-hoo. Stick left me.

400
00:24:27,888 --> 00:24:31,141
Think I'll bury my sorrows
between the legs of a supermodel."

401
00:24:31,224 --> 00:24:32,308
Don't push it, Stick.

402
00:24:32,393 --> 00:24:34,310
Or what?

403
00:24:34,395 --> 00:24:36,563
I'm trying to teach you how to stay alive.

404
00:24:36,647 --> 00:24:38,732
Christ, you're worse than your old man.

405
00:24:38,815 --> 00:24:41,402
Born to lose Battlin' Jack.

406
00:24:41,485 --> 00:24:44,488
At least your daddy got
paid when he hit the floor.

407
00:24:46,948 --> 00:24:48,241
You're hurting me.

408
00:24:48,324 --> 00:24:50,368
Make me stop.

409
00:24:50,452 --> 00:24:52,287
- I can't.
- Then quit.

410
00:24:52,370 --> 00:24:54,164
Murdocks never quit.

411
00:24:58,293 --> 00:24:59,420
Then beat me.

412
00:25:00,712 --> 00:25:03,424
I've got all day, kid.

413
00:25:05,091 --> 00:25:06,635
You're just a bully.

414
00:25:06,718 --> 00:25:10,639
World's full of 'em. What
are you gonna do about it?

415
00:25:12,140 --> 00:25:13,141
Feel the breeze.

416
00:25:17,688 --> 00:25:19,355
You got heart, kid.

417
00:25:20,273 --> 00:25:21,775
But heart's not enough.

418
00:25:21,858 --> 00:25:24,110
You've got to control that rage.

419
00:25:24,194 --> 00:25:25,403
You said anger's a weapon.

420
00:25:25,487 --> 00:25:27,948
Anger is a spark, good.

421
00:25:28,031 --> 00:25:33,537
Rage is a wildfire, out of
control, therefore useless.

422
00:25:33,620 --> 00:25:35,664
Just like you laying there.

423
00:25:45,841 --> 00:25:47,926
I thought Murdocks never quit.

424
00:25:50,303 --> 00:25:52,889
It's my fault! It's my fault!

425
00:25:52,973 --> 00:25:54,475
I did it, I killed him!

426
00:25:54,558 --> 00:25:55,601
Killed who?

427
00:25:55,684 --> 00:25:57,393
My dad.

428
00:25:59,938 --> 00:26:01,898
They paid him to lose against Creel.

429
00:26:01,982 --> 00:26:04,568
But... But I wanted him to win.

430
00:26:04,651 --> 00:26:06,361
So he did because of me.

431
00:26:06,444 --> 00:26:08,196
Because of me.

432
00:26:10,031 --> 00:26:11,992
I just wanted him to come home.

433
00:26:12,075 --> 00:26:14,327
But he didn't, and he never will.

434
00:26:14,410 --> 00:26:17,038
We all pay for our choices, kid.

435
00:26:17,998 --> 00:26:22,168
Maybe your old man fought for
you, maybe he did it for himself.

436
00:26:22,252 --> 00:26:26,089
The only thing you know
for sure is he's gone now.

437
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:28,967
But I'm here.

438
00:26:30,010 --> 00:26:32,262
Now, get up.

439
00:26:32,345 --> 00:26:35,682
Time to stop taking a
beating and start giving one.

440
00:26:37,433 --> 00:26:39,227
Get up.

441
00:26:42,063 --> 00:26:43,273
Get up.

442
00:26:45,150 --> 00:26:46,359
Get up!

443
00:26:54,450 --> 00:26:58,496
Come on, kid. Show me
I'm not wasting my time.

444
00:27:13,679 --> 00:27:16,682
Took you 20 years to learn
how to get out of that one.

445
00:27:17,599 --> 00:27:19,350
Yeah, I've learned a lot
since you've been gone.

446
00:27:19,434 --> 00:27:20,936
- Like what?
- You're a dick.

447
00:27:21,019 --> 00:27:23,104
That's true.

448
00:27:23,188 --> 00:27:24,439
You got any beer?

449
00:27:25,065 --> 00:27:26,817
Yeah, in the fridge.

450
00:27:28,401 --> 00:27:29,485
I'll bet...

451
00:27:30,821 --> 00:27:34,074
it's that German piss, isn't it?

452
00:27:35,075 --> 00:27:37,535
So you gonna tell me why you're here?

453
00:27:37,619 --> 00:27:40,330
Or is the suspense supposed to kill me?

454
00:27:41,247 --> 00:27:43,458
It's the war, Matty.

455
00:27:47,754 --> 00:27:49,214
Never-ending war.

456
00:27:49,297 --> 00:27:51,424
With who? You never
got around to that part.

457
00:27:51,507 --> 00:27:54,761
Now, the Japanese, mostly.

458
00:27:54,845 --> 00:27:58,431
Look, I don't want you tearing up
Hell's Kitchen going after the yakuza.

459
00:27:58,514 --> 00:28:00,016
Yakuza?

460
00:28:00,976 --> 00:28:03,812
You don't know what's going
on in your own backyard.

461
00:28:03,895 --> 00:28:07,190
The guy that was yappin' with
that old man you slapped around,

462
00:28:07,273 --> 00:28:08,399
he's pretty high up.

463
00:28:08,483 --> 00:28:12,237
He goes by a lot of names.
Using Nobu this time around.

464
00:28:13,404 --> 00:28:14,530
So, Nobu,

465
00:28:14,615 --> 00:28:16,992
you want him so bad, why'd you let
him get away back in the garage?

466
00:28:17,075 --> 00:28:18,534
I don't want him.

467
00:28:18,619 --> 00:28:22,038
I want what's on the ship he's
meeting at the docks tonight.

468
00:28:22,122 --> 00:28:24,249
Right, Owlsley was talking about that.

469
00:28:25,291 --> 00:28:27,669
What's Nobu bringing
in? Drugs or something?

470
00:28:27,753 --> 00:28:29,420
A weapon.

471
00:28:29,504 --> 00:28:32,340
They call it Black Sky,
the bringer of shadows.

472
00:28:32,423 --> 00:28:33,424
What kind of weapon?

473
00:28:33,508 --> 00:28:36,094
The kind you don't want in your world.

474
00:28:37,763 --> 00:28:38,805
Just say it.

475
00:28:38,889 --> 00:28:40,932
- Say what?
- Say that you want my help.

476
00:28:41,016 --> 00:28:43,434
I want you to help yourself.

477
00:28:43,518 --> 00:28:46,104
Nobu and his guys are in tight with Fisk.

478
00:28:46,187 --> 00:28:48,564
You hurt them, you hurt baldy...

479
00:28:48,649 --> 00:28:50,566
You know about Fisk?

480
00:28:50,651 --> 00:28:51,943
I know a lot of shit.

481
00:28:52,027 --> 00:28:55,030
This beer, for example, sucks.

482
00:28:55,113 --> 00:28:59,075
After all your talk about
cutting friends loose, and...

483
00:28:59,910 --> 00:29:00,952
now you need one.

484
00:29:01,036 --> 00:29:04,665
I don't need a friend. I
need a soldier. Committed.

485
00:29:04,748 --> 00:29:07,709
Not some bleeding heart idealist
hanging onto half measures.

486
00:29:07,793 --> 00:29:10,461
You don't know anything
about what I'm doing here.

487
00:29:10,545 --> 00:29:13,256
Kid, in war, people die.

488
00:29:13,339 --> 00:29:16,176
If it's not you, it's the guy next to you.

489
00:29:18,469 --> 00:29:22,724
How many men have you
killed protecting this city?

490
00:29:27,395 --> 00:29:29,815
You're still afraid to cross that line.

491
00:29:29,898 --> 00:29:33,359
Someday, it's gonna come
down to you or the other guy.

492
00:29:33,443 --> 00:29:35,862
If it's not Fisk, somebody else.

493
00:29:35,946 --> 00:29:37,530
What're you gonna do then?

494
00:29:37,613 --> 00:29:40,992
Yeah, a Russian asshole asked
me the same thing recently...

495
00:29:41,076 --> 00:29:42,452
right before he died.

496
00:29:42,535 --> 00:29:44,996
Are you the one that put him in the ground?

497
00:29:45,496 --> 00:29:46,581
No.

498
00:29:48,166 --> 00:29:50,001
Half measures, Matty.

499
00:29:51,586 --> 00:29:53,546
Ah, screw it.

500
00:29:54,923 --> 00:29:57,258
Ride with me tonight...

501
00:29:57,342 --> 00:30:00,428
help me destroy Black Sky,
keep it off the streets,

502
00:30:00,511 --> 00:30:02,555
and I promise you this...

503
00:30:02,638 --> 00:30:06,351
Wilson Fisk will know the taste
of fear the day he faces you

504
00:30:06,434 --> 00:30:09,980
'cause he'll know that you
kicked the guy he's afraid of

505
00:30:10,063 --> 00:30:11,732
right in the nuts.

506
00:30:13,608 --> 00:30:14,860
What do you say, kid?

507
00:30:16,319 --> 00:30:17,612
One rule...

508
00:30:18,571 --> 00:30:19,865
you don't kill anybody.

509
00:30:22,658 --> 00:30:26,621
I swear I will not kill anybody.

510
00:30:30,125 --> 00:30:31,376
Pussy.

511
00:30:37,173 --> 00:30:38,299
Uh...

512
00:30:38,383 --> 00:30:41,219
How's your head?

513
00:30:41,302 --> 00:30:42,637
I'm alive.

514
00:30:42,721 --> 00:30:44,597
It's enough.

515
00:30:45,724 --> 00:30:47,934
How much do I owe you for the groceries?

516
00:30:48,018 --> 00:30:51,479
No, no,
no, no, no. Put that away.

517
00:30:51,562 --> 00:30:53,314
I don't want your money.

518
00:30:53,398 --> 00:30:55,734
No, I don't take charity.

519
00:30:55,817 --> 00:30:57,568
All right.

520
00:30:57,652 --> 00:31:00,238
You can pay me if you want...

521
00:31:00,321 --> 00:31:01,656
with information?

522
00:31:02,198 --> 00:31:03,950
What can I tell you?

523
